cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CE, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an end-to-end model for predicting drug-drug interactions using graph-augmented convolutional networks. This involves training a machine learning model to learn the structural relations between drug pairs and make predictions. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The use of machine learning techniques to predict drug-drug interactions falls under the scope of artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract information from drug interaction databases. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper applies computational techniques to the field of drug discovery and development. 
5. cs.DB (Databases): The paper involves the use of drug interaction databases to train and evaluate the proposed model.
